IBM-PC BIOS
Most of what the BIOS does is related to Input/Output, where its function is to
present the programmer with simpler, more machine and device independent I/O
operations.  The IBM-PC BIOS uses software interrupts 10h ~ 1Ah, 40h to accomplish various
operations. Therefore, the INT 10h ~ INT 1Ah and INT 40h instructions provide
the interface to BIOS. The following table summarizes the BIOS services: